    "L6_top_supported_1": "De Sitter space is an Einstein manifold since the Ricci tensor is proportional to the metric:\n\nR_{\\mu\\nu} = R^\\lambda{}_{\\mu\\lambda\\nu} = \\frac{n - 1}{\\alpha^2}g_{\\mu\\nu}\n\nThis means de Sitter space is a vacuum solution of Einstein's equation with cosmological constant given by\n\n\\Lambda = \\frac{(n - 1)(n - 2)}{2\\alpha^2}.",
    "L6_top_supported_2": "The Riemann curvature tensor of de Sitter space is given by\n\nR_{\\rho\\sigma\\mu\\nu} = {1 \\over \\alpha^2}\\left(g_{\\rho\\mu}g_{\\sigma\\nu} - g_{\\rho\\nu}g_{\\sigma\\mu}\\right)\n\n(using the sign convention \n R^{\\rho}{}_{\\sigma\\mu\\nu} =\n \\partial_{\\mu}\\Gamma^{\\rho}_{\\nu\\sigma} -\n \\partial_{\\nu}\\Gamma^{\\rho}_{\\mu\\sigma} +\n \\Gamma^{\\rho}_{\\mu\\lambda}\\Gamma^{\\lambda}_{\\nu\\sigma} -\n \\Gamma^{\\rho}_{\\nu\\lambda}\\Gamma^{\\lambda}_{\\mu\\sigma}\n for the Riemann curvature tensor).",
    "L6_top_risky_1": "Every maximally symmetric space has constant curvature.",
    "L6_top_risky_2": "* De Sitter universe\n* AdS/CFT correspondence\n* De Sitter–Schwarzschild metric",
